The paper focuses on maximizing the throughput performance of an ambient backscatter communication system, which involves wireless communication and energy harvesting. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a reinforcement learning approach to solve the problem, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper models the problem as a Markov Decision Process (MDP), which is a common technique in control systems (cs.SY).
